; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures USART as UART and receives data.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting ports with a suitable instrument should be correct
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. USART
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. USART1  : PC7 (Transmit)
;               : PC8 (Receive)
;
; E. Port Connection
;    1. PC7 (Transmit  / StarterKit 1) <----> PC8 (Receive / StarterKit 2)
;    2. PC8 (Receive / StarterKit 1)  <----> PC7 (Transmit / StarterKit 2)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; USART1
; 1. Channel                   : 1 (USART1)
;
; 2. Config                    : [ 1 i u 8 n 1 n 38400 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    USART Mode                : u (UART)
;    Data Bit                  : 8 (8bit)
;    Parity                    : n (None)
;    Stop Bit                  : 1 (1bit)
;    Speed Mode                : n (Normal)
;    Baudrate                  : 38400 bps
;
; 3. Rx                        : [ 1 8 ]
;    Receive Data Length       : 8
;
; PCU (PCx)
; 1. Port Group                : 2 (PCU Port C)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 2 8 a 4 -pupd p ] [ 2 7 a 4 -pupd p ]
;    Pin Number                : 8 / 7
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 4 (RX/TX)
;    Pull-up/down              : p (Pull-up)
;
; PCU (PCx)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 2 8 a 4 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 2 7 a 4 -pupd p'
mpause 30

; USART1
sendln 'cm usart'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 1'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 1 i u 8 n 1 n 38400'
mpause 30
sendln 'rx 1 8'
